criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Enrolled in diabetes disease management program

          -  ages 30-70

          -  HbA1c between 7.5% and 10.9% in the previous six months

          -  an Internet or 3G connection and email address;

          -  a working phone line (land line or cellular); and

          -  ability to read and understand the English language.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  taking insulin;

          -  inability to independently engage in self-management behaviors (diagnosis of dementia,
             severe depression, schizophrenia, or cognitive impairment);

          -  severe complications, which would preclude achieving an HbA1c goal of 7% including
             diagnosis of the following:

          -  severe stroke;

          -  heart failure;

          -  end-stage renal disease;

          -  kidney dialysis; and

          -  legally blind.
